network_overview: At the IMS_SIGNALING observation point, only SIP/UDP signaling is captured for four VoLTE/VoNR call attempts; no media/user-plane protocols are present in this trace. All observed call attempts show an initial INVITE receiving a 100 response and then a SIP 407 response (with Reason: Q.850;cause=21,SIP;cause=407), followed by a new INVITE attempt that reaches 183/180 and PRACK/200(PRACK), but no call reaches a final 200 OK to the INVITE; two dialogs are later cancelled by the caller with CANCEL and end with 487 Request Terminated.

pattern_matches.pattern_name: SIP Proxy Authentication Required challenge during session initiation
evidence: Call mpikejiky...: 407 Response at 1765805291.005 with code "Q.850;cause=21,SIP;cause=407" after INVITE/100
Call asbcmpike...: 407 Response at 1765805291.004 with code "Q.850;cause=21,SIP;cause=407" after INVITE/100
Call mwm1jee...: 407 Response at 1765805409.862 with code "Q.850;cause=21,SIP;cause=407" after INVITE/100
Call asbcmwm1...: 407 Response at 1765805409.861 with code "Q.850;cause=21,SIP;cause=407" after INVITE/100
pattern_matches.explanation: Multiple INVITE transactions explicitly receive SIP 407 responses, demonstrating a proxy authentication challenge is present in the signaling path. The capture does not include headers to confirm whether the subsequent INVITE contained valid proxy authorization, so only the existence of the 407 challenge (not its resolution) is proven.

pattern_matches.pattern_name: Caller-initiated cancellation of early dialog (CANCEL -> 487 Request Terminated)
evidence: Call mpikejiky...: CANCEL at 1765805316.794 followed by 200 Response (to CANCEL) at 1765805316.794 and 487 Response at 1765805316.794; ACK at 1765805316.806
Call asbcmpike...: CANCEL at 1765805316.795 followed by 200 Response (to CANCEL) at 1765805316.811 and 487 Response at 1765805316.813; ACK at 1765805316.813
pattern_matches.explanation: The SIP sequence explicitly shows CANCEL being sent and acknowledged with 200, and the original INVITE transaction being terminated with 487, which is the standard SIP behavior for cancelling an in-progress INVITE.

observations.finding: All four call attempts receive SIP 407 (Proxy Authentication Required) shortly after the first INVITE, each with Reason header content "Q.850;cause=21,SIP;cause=407".
After the 407, a subsequent INVITE attempt is observed that progresses to provisional responses (183 and 180) and reliable provisional handling (PRACK followed by 200 Response).
Two dialogs are explicitly cancelled by the caller after ~25.8s, ending with 487 Request Terminated.

Two dialogs end within ~0.93s and do not show CANCEL/487 or any final response to the INVITE in the provided message list; the trace marks them as INVITE_SETUP_TIMEOUT but this is not directly evidenced by an on-wire SIP timeout response.
observations.evidence: Calls mwm1jee... and asbcmwm1... end at 1765805410.746/1765805410.745 after last observed message 180 Response, with no subsequent final response captured

root_causes.issue: SIP 407 Proxy Authentication Required encountered during call setup
root_causes.description: Each call attempt shows the initial INVITE being challenged by a SIP 407 response (Proxy Authentication Required) with Reason content "Q.850;cause=21,SIP;cause=407". This indicates the SIP proxy requires authentication for the transaction as observed at the IMS signaling capture point.
root_causes.impact: Can prevent successful call establishment if the subsequent INVITE does not include valid authentication credentials; even when provisional responses are later seen, no call reaches a final 200 OK to the INVITE in this capture.
root_causes.confidence_justification: Direct packet-level evidence of SIP 407 responses is present in 4/4 call attempts. What is not proven from this dataset is whether authentication was correctly provided on the re-INVITE, because no relevant authorization headers are included in the provided evidence and no final 200 OK to INVITE is observed.

root_causes.issue: Calls cancelled by caller before completion (CANCEL -> 487)
root_causes.description: For two calls, the caller side sent CANCEL with Reason "Q.850;cause=16;text=normal call clearing" which was answered with 200 Response and then the original INVITE was terminated with 487 Response, followed by ACK. This is consistent with caller aborting the call setup while still in early dialog (only provisional responses observed).
root_causes.impact: Call setup fails; no session is established.
root_causes.confidence_justification: Direct evidence of CANCEL, 200 (to CANCEL), and 487 (to INVITE) is present with precise timestamps for both affected calls.

inconclusive_aspects.aspect: Why no call reaches a final 200 OK to INVITE (call establishment)
inconclusive_aspects.reason: The capture shows provisional responses (183/180) and PRACK handling but does not include any final response to INVITE (e.g., 200 OK) nor any explicit error response explaining failure beyond the initial 407 challenge; for two short calls, the trace ends after 180 without further signaling.
inconclusive_aspects.additional_capture_needed: Full SIP dialog including final responses to INVITE (and any retransmissions), plus SIP headers relevant to authentication on the post-407 INVITE (e.g., proxy authorization fields) at the same IMS signaling point.

inconclusive_aspects.reason: This observation point is IMS signaling only; no RTP is captured and no SDP media is detected in the provided evidence, so media/ringback tone cannot be validated from this trace.
inconclusive_aspects.additional_capture_needed: A capture point that includes media packets (RTP) and/or full SIP bodies with SDP to verify early media indications.

inconclusive_aspects.reason: Only SIP is detected and GTP tunnels are 0; user-plane is not observable at this capture point.
inconclusive_aspects.additional_capture_needed: User-plane capture where applicable (e.g., interfaces carrying user-plane traffic) to observe whether media/bearers are established.

recommendations.action: Investigate why SIP 407 challenges occur for every INVITE and verify the subsequent INVITE includes correct authentication (collect SIP headers for the challenged and re-attempted INVITEs).
recommendations.rationale: All calls show explicit SIP 407 responses; persistent challenges without successful final call establishment suggests an authentication handling issue is plausible but not provable without the missing header details and final INVITE outcome.

recommendations.action: Extend IMS signaling capture to include the complete call setup until a final response to INVITE is seen (or until the caller times out), ensuring both legs (src/dst IP pairs) are captured continuously.
recommendations.rationale: Two calls are marked as timeouts but the on-wire evidence in the provided message list ends at 180; capturing the missing portion will confirm whether final responses were absent, delayed, or lost outside the capture scope.

recommendations.action: If ringback/audio is a reported symptom, capture at a point where SIP with SDP and media packets are observable for the same call attempt.
recommendations.rationale: No SDP and no RTP are present here, so ringback/early media cannot be confirmed from this capture.

Provisional signaling (183/180) and reliable provisional handling (PRACK->200) are observed after re-INVITEs.
